STRATEGY DESIGN PATTERN:

It is a behaviroal design pattern that define muliple algorithm, encapsulate their logic in dedicated class and enables changing an algorithm's behaviour at runtime

Scenario:
A vechicle class(Super class) with a method drive()- Maybe sports,normal,offroad mode
1. When tow or more subclass like SportsVehichle,OffroadVehichle initialy have the same drive() - It creates CODE DUPLICATION. Since here there is only 2 classes its okay but if huge classes use the same drive() it takes more memory
2. When the user what to modify the drive function for OffroadVehicle from sports to offroad ,the class have to modified it create TIGHT COUPLING 

Solution:
Have a interface DriveStrategy that contains abstract method drive()
1. Muliple classes can implement the drive() in their classes -It will be helpfull for creating new Strategy like NormalDrive and more 
2.We create Vechile class that has a reference of DriveStrategy
Since it is an reference we can modify the DriveStrategies at runtime.

